ning room reportedly fell silent as he crossed it. A public subscription paid for a portrait and a marble bust in his honor.","number":4},{"category":"science","header":"A historian consulted him on George the Third","body":"George Bancroft sought Woodward's expert opinion on the madness of King George the Third for his history of the United States. Woodward also lectured for temperance and called early for asylums to treat inebriates.","number":5}],"education":[{"institution_id":"INST022","type":"honorary_degree","dates":"1822","notes":"Honorary Doctor of Medicine from Yale College."}],"career":[{"role":"Prison physician","organization":"Connecticut State Prison","start_year":1827,"end_year":1832,"notes":"Physician at the state prison in Wethersfield."},{"role":"Superintendent","organization":"Worcester State Lunatic Hospital","start_year":1832,"end_year":1846,"notes":"First superintendent of the first state asylum in Massachusetts."},{"role":"First President","organization":"Association of Medical Superintendents of American Institutions for the Insane","start_year":1844,"end_year":1848,"notes":"The body later became the American Psychiatric Association."},{"role":"State Senator","organization":"Connecticut State Senate","start_year":1832,"end_year":1833,"notes":"Represented the Hartford district."}],"slug":"samuel-woodward-1787"},"HD2442":{"id":"HD2442","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":7,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"parents":{"father_id":"HD2432","mother_id":"X00803"},"tags":[],"sources":[],"birth":{"year":1797,"month":7,"city":"Hadley","state":"Massachusetts"},"death":{"year":1873,"month":10},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"X00804","children_ids":["HD2463","HD2464","HD2443","HD2465","HD2466","HD2444","HD2462","HD2467","HD2468","HD2469","HD2470"],"marriage_number":1,"date